<!--
VOICING PLAN — Hosanna, Loud Hosanna (Bb major)
================================================

PHRASE 1 (mm. 1-5): Light opening, "43" and "334" patterns
- m1 pickup: V open fifth (F C) in RH, F C F in LH — airy introduction
- m2: I "33" root pos in RH (Bb D), "334" in LH (Bb F Bb) — settled tonic
- m3: Four-chord bar; LH uses stacked thirds for each chord change
- m4: IV → I → IIm → V stepwise in both hands; LH stays in bass register
- m5: I maj7 ("333") in LH for added richness on the sustained high D

PHRASE 2 (mm. 6-9): Parallel verse, contrasting voicings
- m6: I "43" 1st inversion (D F Bb) in RH gives different color vs m2
- m7: VIm → IIm → V → I; smooth stepwise voice leading throughout
- m8: IV → VIm → I → V with contrary motion LH↓ / RH↑
- m9: I ascending arpeggio in RH (Bb D F); LH "334" four notes held

PHRASE 3 (mm. 10-13): Chorus — fuller texture, wider range
- m10: V → I → IV with RH in upper register (C5-G5 range)
- m11: V climax with F A C in RH (three-note chord), LH four notes
- m12: Same harmony as m10 but with 4-note LH on IV (Eb Bb G Bb)
- m13: V sus4 ("44" quartal) in RH for color; LH full four-note V sustained

PHRASE 4 (mm. 14-17): Final verse — maximum texture, root-pos cadence
- m14: I maj7 ("333") LH — richest moment so far
- m15: Fuller chords throughout; IIm7 ("233" pattern) for color
- m16: Climax — 4-note LH on IV (Eb Bb Eb G), 3-note RH on VIm
- m17: Final I "334" root position in LH; I root pos in RH — convergence

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS
========================
- Inner alto voice (RH lower): Bb→D→G→F→Bb across phrases 1-2
  maintains smooth contrary motion with LH bass
- LH bass line: F-Bb-G-C-F in m3 follows ii-V-I arpeggiation
- m8-9: LH descends Eb→G→Bb→F while RH ascends Eb→Bb→F — contrary motion
- m15-16: LH builds to 4-note chords, RH fills upper register; maximum density
  before the final convergence in m17

TEXTURE ARC
===========
- mm. 1-5:   Light (2-3 RH, 3 LH). Pickup V → I establishes key.
- mm. 6-9:   Moderate. First inversion in RH adds harmonic color.
- mm. 10-13: Chorus. RH moves to upper register; 3-note chords.
              LH reaches 4 notes on strong beats.
- mm. 14-17: Full (3 RH, 4 LH). Climax on IV in m16.
              Final convergence to Bb root position.
-->
